From: SDDC_FX3 maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] rx888: poll for re-enumeration after firmware upload, then settle

The post-upload `sleep(1)` is a single-shot guess and the comment in
the source admits as much:

    sleep(1); // how long should this be?

On Linux hosts FX3 boot + udev settle can exceed 1 s (more so under
Docker bind-mounted /dev/bus/usb), after which the second device-list
scan finds no `0x04b4:0x00f1` entry and `rx888_usb_init()` exits with
"Error or device could not be found".

Replace the fixed sleep with a 200 ms polling loop, capped at ~10 s,
that breaks as soon as the loaded device appears.

A 1 s settle delay after first detection is necessary as well: even
when the loaded PID is visible to `libusb_get_device_list()`, the
kernel's SuperSpeed enumeration sequence (config selection + U1/U2
LPM enable) is still in flight for several hundred milliseconds.
Captured via `usbmon`, the kernel's last setup URBs land ~3 ms after
the device first appears, but udev's libusb-side device-list refresh
lags further.  Without the settle delay, the upstream rescan at
`rx888.c:717` returns a stale list missing `04b4:00f1` and
`rx888_usb_init()` still exits with "Error or device could not be
found" — exactly the original symptom.

Pinned against ka9q-radio commit f78cff9cc8c7fa33ea49aac9176d9263c535a332.
---
 src/rx888.c | 22 +++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/rx888.c b/src/rx888.c
index 0000000..0000000 100644
--- a/src/rx888.c
+++ b/src/rx888.c
@@ -697,7 +697,27 @@
     fprintf(stderr,", loading rx888 firmware file %s",full_firmware_file);
     if(ezusb_load_ram(handle,full_firmware_file,FX_TYPE_FX3,IMG_TYPE_IMG,1) == 0){
       fprintf(stderr,", done\n");
-      sleep(1); // how long should this be?
+      // Poll up to ~10 s for the device to re-enumerate at the loaded PID.
+      for(int waited = 0; waited < 50; waited++){
+        usleep(200000);
+        libusb_device **scan = NULL;
+        ssize_t const n = libusb_get_device_list(NULL, &scan);
+        bool found = false;
+        for(ssize_t i = 0; i < n; i++){
+          struct libusb_device_descriptor d = {0};
+          if(libusb_get_device_descriptor(scan[i], &d) == 0
+             && d.idVendor == Vendor_id && d.idProduct == Loaded_product_id){
+            found = true; break;
+          }
+        }
+        libusb_free_device_list(scan, 1);
+        if(found){
+          // Let kernel SuperSpeed LPM setup + udev device-list refresh
+          // complete before the upstream rescan at rx888.c:717 runs.
+          sleep(1);
+          break;
+        }
+      }
     } else {
       fprintf(stderr,", failed for device %d.%d (logical)\n",
 	      libusb_get_bus_number(device),libusb_get_device_address(device));
